main event: A civilian couple observed a football-shaped UFO in Mensey, New York, on October 6, 1966.
interesting points: The object was traveling toward the north when it suddenly turned northeast and climbed rapidly., Observers reported a white flash before the object disappeared., The sighting lasted for several minutes., The couple had previous encounters with UFOs and claimed to have expert knowledge in aviation., No photographs or physical evidence were collected with the report.
witness description: a civilian couple with expertise in aviation
